- gate-oslo-incubator-python26 http://logs.openstack.org/72/55672/4/check/gate-oslo-incubator-python26/592b182 : SUCCESS in 3m 57s
- gate-oslo-incubator-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/72/55672/4/check/gate-oslo-incubator-python27/0cc12fa : SUCCESS in 3m 02s
'}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2013-11-13 15:08:12.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

logging doesn't use time.asctime(), it calls time.strftime() with an explicit format string (http://hg.python.org/cpython/file/c163e5011bd3/Lib/logging/__init__.py#l423). So my concern about the locale isn't relevant.

The format code %f is, however, not understood by time.strftime().

    >>> time.strftime('%S,%f', time.localtime())
    '14,f'

The default behavior in logging uses a hard-coded format string and includes the sub-second value after a comma by accessing the msecs attribute of the log record. I suspect this is the reason the original patch did not include %f in the date format -- the required value is not in the time information, but in the log record.

Oslo logging provides a date format string without an explicit reference for the sub-second value, but the value is being logged anyway. Where is the value coming from?"}, {'account_id': 7537, 'date': '2013-11-14 13:35:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Abandoned

I'm doing it wrong... :)

This can be set in the log_config file as follows:

[formatter_context]
format = %(asctime)s.s(msec)%03d %(process)d %(levelname)s %(name)s [%(request_id)s %(user)s %(tenant)s] %(instance)s%(message)s
datefmt = %Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S
class = nova.openstack.common.log.ContextFormatter
args = (datefmt=datefmt)

Sorry for any inconvenience - change abandoned..."}]

commit_message:
Remove (msecs) from the date format

When migrating from the "built-in" logging to using logging_config
in Nova, the log file format changes from "2013-11-08 14:29:49.730"
to "2013-11-08 14:29:49,730.730"

This was put in as part of I135213cad3ec21edf8934c1094ee84ac93ed4561
to troubleshoot an issue however it probably should have been added
to the _DEFAULT_LOG_DATE_FORMAT instead of being added to each
formatter.

This change moves it to the sensible default and is now effectively
a NOOP.

Closes-bug: #1249388

Change-Id: I026ba663a098b92825390c26aff625e5b1f9f35b

commit_message:
Freeze iso8601 for older stable

As explained in Iece0116d3c412216251e2d7fbffe10bfe2c1c789
master bumped iso8601 version requirement to 0.1.8
but we can't do that on older stable branches, so cap the version instead.

Change-Id: I5677a294a1428774fc5c3b767bd4a7c8567d02ff

commit_message:
Convert to a more modern form of openstack-common.conf

One module per line is the new hotness. I've also sorted the
modules alphabetically. There are no changes to your imports, but
this makes it easier for oslo maintainers to keep your imports up
to date.

Change-Id: I6e9ae5d8b953b81014bd60cc842af33c6af58b61

commit_message:
domainEventRegisterAny called too often

Changeid I090765802bfe443440f16722bc7c43b6280fe56a fixes
bug #1240905 but introduced a bug whereby domainEventRegisterAny
is called on every call to _get_connection.

Change-Id: Ifafc6a4c172b1521d62988ccbb3a2f51a95e323f
Fixes: bug #1250135

commit_message:
Add policy style '@'/'!' rules to prop protections

A value of '@' will always allow the corresponding operation for a
property, and '!' will always disallow the operation.

Related to blueprint api-v2-property-protection

DocImpact

Change-Id: I1196a58a6f97cd0856bf97463386776a00359a49

instance, create an internal snapshot in the qcow image, extract the

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary steps for cold snapshots

Up until now when we created cold snapshots we were stopping the
instance, create an internal snapshot, extract the snapshot to a file
and then delete the internal snapshot before bringing up the instance.

If the instance is shut down, there's no concurrent writer, so the image
can be directly extracted without taking an internal snapshot first,
because the snapshot and the current state are the same.

In this patch the creation and deletion of the internal snapshot are
removed to eliminate the extra steps and optimize the creation of
snapshots a bit.

Closes-Bug: #1242819
Closes-Bug: #1247185

Change-Id: I429fa2e1e26aea321eecbf14edd11263fff525ae

commit_message:
mongodb, db2: do not print full URL in logs

The full URL used to connect to MongoDB or DB2 might contains sensitive
information such as username and password, so it's better to not print
it at all.
Instead, just print the hosts that are being connected to.

Fixes-Bug: #1244476

Change-Id: I092be52a760cc97a9c3e6357d19609b8886e3175

commit_message:
Fixes error message encoding issue when using qpid

Making the message only consist of primitive types
before sending it by qpid.

Fixes bug 1242734

Change-Id: I3ff7a19af9a7671f955345ada6acfba8bf573c70
(cherry picked from commit 94b9e66360387d24548f165cc4c7ee67f5160a0c)

commit_message:
Add some log messages to capabilities_filter.py

There is no log message in capabilities_filter.py when host did not
pass this filter. It is better add some log messages in this file
to improve debug ability.

Change-Id: Ie57a8882a69f7914e67871a188d664cd6949538f
